article.headline: Jacksonville 83, Lipscomb 67
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Ben Smith scored 18 points and Jacksonville beat Lipscomb 83-67 on Saturday. The Dolphins (2-5, 2-0 Atlantic Sun) shot 51.6 percent (33 of 64), including a 7-for-9 night by Smith. Travis Cohn, who added 14 points on 7 of 10 shooting, while Ayron Hardy scored 13 and Lehmon Colbert had 11 for Jacksonville. The Bisons (3-4, 1-1) were led by 17 points from Brandon Brown. Josh Slater and Adnan Hodzic added 13 and 12, respectively. Jacksonville outrebounded Lipscomb 38-24, while grabbing 16 offensive boards. The Dolphins, who overcame a 19-point deficit to defeat Belmont on Thursday, led the Bisons 30-21 at halftime.
